# Local-development environment template — copy to .env.local and replace
# only the values you need to override. .env.local IS gitignored; this file
# (.env.local.example) IS committed.
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.local.example .env.local
#   # ... edit .env.local with real values ...
#   ./scripts/local_scan_test.sh
#
# Format: one KEY=VALUE per line. NO angle brackets in values — the script
# parses this file line by line and treats anything after `=` as the literal
# value, but please keep the values shell-safe (no unmatched quotes, etc.).

# --- Anthropic Claude API ---
# Get from https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# Local-dev key only — never use the production Phrase Enterprise key here.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-replace-with-real-key

# --- GitHub App (gate path) ---
# Replace these only if you're testing the real /agent/scan endpoint against
# live GitHub. For /agent/test-scan (LOCAL_TEST_MODE) they can stay as the
# placeholders below — the test endpoint bypasses GitHub.
GITHUB_APP_ID=placeholder
GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY=placeholder
GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=placeholder
GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=placeholder

# --- Deployment-gate bearer token ---
# Local dev: any non-empty string is fine. Must match the Authorization
# header the local_scan_test.sh script sends (default: local-test-token).
PHRASE_SCAN_TOKEN=local-test-token

# --- Optional Slack webhook (BR-002 bypass alerts) ---
# Leave commented to disable Slack locally — the scanner logs a warning
# instead of failing the bypass.
# SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/...

# --- LLM provider selection (Appendix D-15 — DEVIATION, sim-only) ---
# THIS is how you switch the model family. Leave everything below commented
# (or unset) for the spec-default Anthropic Claude path — production
# behaviour is unchanged. Uncomment to switch.
#
#   SCANNER_LLM_PROVIDER : anthropic (default) | openai | google
#   SCANNER_LLM_MODEL    : optional model override (else the provider default)
#
# DATA GOVERNANCE: the Zero-Data-Retention + DPA assurances are confirmed for
# Anthropic ONLY. Selecting openai/google sends source to a provider without
# that guarantee — off by default, loudly warned, pending Security/Legal
# sign-off. You must also supply that provider's key below, or the service
# fails fast on startup (it never silently falls back to Claude).
#
# SCANNER_LLM_PROVIDER=openai
# SCANNER_LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
#
# SCANNER_LLM_PROVIDER=google
# SCANNER_LLM_MODEL=gemini-2.5-pro
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=...
